The paper discusses the design and evaluation of an automated triage system for medical symptoms, which involves computational modelling, medical insights, and validation and testing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). Among these, cs.HC is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design and evaluation of a system that interacts with users to provide medical advice. The other categories are also relevant as they involve computational modelling, data analysis, and natural language processing, which are used in the development and evaluation of the system.
